 soca song \"Hot Hot Hot\"\nBULLET::::- Vladimir Farrell, association footballer\nBULLET::::- Howard A. Fergus, author, poet and three time acting governor of Montserrat\nBULLET::::- Patricia Griffin, pioneer nurse and volunteer social worker, honored on a 2006 series of stamps recognizing notable citizens\nBULLET::::- George Irish, writer, human rights activist\nBULLET::::- Helen Joseph, Miss Montserrat 1964 and Top 16 in Miss World 1964\nBULLET::::- E. A. Markham, poet and author\nBULLET::::- Dean Mason, association footballer\nBULLET::::- Shane Ryan, writer, human rights activist\nBULLET::::- M. P. Shiel, writer\nBULLET::::- Lyle Taylor, association footballer\nBULLET::::- Maizie Williams, member of pop group Boney M\nBULLET::::- Angela Yee, member of Power 105.1's morning show, the Breakfast Club\n\nBULLET::::- Bibliography of Montserrat\nBULLET::::- Index of Montserrat-related articles\nBULLET::::- Outline of Montserrat\n\nGovernment\nBULLET::::- Government of Montserrat\nBULLET::::- Montserrat National Trust\nBULLET::::- Premier of Montserrat\n\nGeneral information\nBULLET::::- Montserrat from \"UCB Libraries GovPubs\".\nBULLET::::- Montserrat Webdirectory\nBULLET::::- Story of the black Irish in Montserrat\n\nNews media\nBULLET::::- Montserrat Reporter news site\nBULLET::::- Radio Montserrat—ZJB Listen live online\n\nTravel\nBULLET::::- Montserrat Tourist Board\nBULLET::::- Montserrat Magazine Publications\nBULLET::::- Montserrat Magazine\n\nHealth reports\nBULLET::::- Toxicity of volcanic ash from Montserrat by RT Cullen, AD Jones, BG Miller, CL Tran, JMG Davis, K Donaldson, M Wilson, V Stone, and A Morgan. Institute of Occupational Medicine Research Report TM/02/01.\nBULLET::::- A Health Survey of Workers on the Island of Montserrat by HA Cowie, MK Graham, A Searl, BG Miller, PA Hutchison, C Swales, S Dempsey, and M Russell. Institute of Occupational Medicine Research Report TM/02/02.\nBULLET::::- A Health Survey of Montserratians Relocated to the UK by HA 