efense (b. 1917)\nBULLET::::- 2009 – Maurice Jarre, French-American composer and conductor (b. 1924)\nBULLET::::- 2010 – June Havoc, American actress, dancer, and director (b. 1912)\nBULLET::::- 2011 – Wenche Foss, Norwegian actress (b. 1917)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – John Arden, English author and playwright (b. 1930)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Alexander Arutiunian, Armenian pianist and composer (b. 1920)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Harry Crews, American novelist, playwright, short story writer, and essayist (b. 1935)\nBULLET::::- 2012 – Addie L. Wyatt, African American labor leader (b. 1924)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – George E. P. Box, English-American statistician and educator (b. 1919)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Manuel García Ferré, Spanish-Argentinian director, producer, and screenwriter (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Richard Griffiths, English actor (b. 1947)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Art Malone, American race car driver (b. 1936)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Hugh McCracken, American guitarist, harmonica player, and producer (b. 1942)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Heinz Patzig, German footballer and manager (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Bob Teague, American college football star and television news-reporter (b. 1929)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Gus Triandos, American baseball player and scout (b. 1930)\nBULLET::::- 2013 – Robert Zildjian, American businessman, founded Sabian (b. 1923)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Jeremiah Denton, American admiral and politician (b. 1924)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Lorenzo Semple, Jr., American screenwriter and producer (b. 1923)\nBULLET::::- 2014 – Avraham Yaski, Israeli architect and academic (b. 1927)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Chuck Brayton, American baseball player and coach (b. 1925)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Joseph Cassidy, Canadian-English priest and academic (b. 1954)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Miroslav Ondříček, Czech cinematographer (b. 1934)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Gene Saks, American actor and director (b. 1921)\nBULLET::::- 2015 – Walter Schuck, German lieutenant and pilot (b. 1920)\nBULLET::::- 2016 – James Noble, Ameri