.1215)\nBULLET::::- 1300 – Blanche of Artois (b. 1248)\nBULLET::::- 1450 – William de la Pole, 1st Duke of Suffolk, English admiral (b. 1396)\nBULLET::::- 1519 – Leonardo da Vinci, Italian painter, sculptor, and architect (b. 1452)\nBULLET::::- 1564 – Rodolfo Pio da Carpi, Italian cardinal (b. 1500)\nBULLET::::- 1627 – Lodovico Grossi da Viadana, Italian composer and educator (b. 1560)\nBULLET::::- 1667 – George Wither, English poet and author (b. 1588)\nBULLET::::- 1683 – Stjepan Gradić, Croatian philosopher and mathematician (b. 1613)\nBULLET::::- 1711 – Laurence Hyde, 1st Earl of Rochester, English politician, First Lord of the Treasury (b. 1641)\nBULLET::::- 1799 – Juan Vicente de Güemes, 2nd Count of Revillagigedo (b. 1740)\nBULLET::::- 1802 – Herman Willem Daendels, Dutch general and politician, Governor-General of the Dutch Gold Coast (b. 1762)\nBULLET::::- 1810 – Henry Jerome de Salis, English priest (b. 1740)\nBULLET::::- 1819 – Mary Moser, English painter and academic (b. 1744)\nBULLET::::- 1857 – Alfred de Musset, French dramatist, poet, and novelist (b. 1810)\nBULLET::::- 1864 – Giacomo Meyerbeer, German composer and educator (b. 1791)\nBULLET::::- 1880 – Eberhard Anheuser, German-American businessman, co-founded Anheuser-Busch (b. 1805)\nBULLET::::- 1880 – Tom Wills, Australian cricketer, co-created Australian rules football (b. 1835)\nBULLET::::- 1885 – Terézia Zakoucs, Hungarian-Slovene author (b. 1817)\nBULLET::::- 1915 – Clara Immerwahr, German chemist (b. 1870)\nBULLET::::- 1918 – Jüri Vilms, Estonian lawyer and politician (b. 1889)\nBULLET::::- 1925 – Antun Branko Šimić, Croatian and Bosnian-Herzegovinian poet (b. 1898)\nBULLET::::- 1927 – Ernest Starling, English physiologist and academic (b. 1866)\nBULLET::::- 1929 – Charalambos Tseroulis, Greek general and politician, Greek Minister for Military Affairs (b. 1879)\nBULLET::::- 1941 – Penelope Delta, Greek author (b. 1874)\nBULLET::::- 1945 – Martin Bormann, German politician (b. 1900)\nBULLET:::